==English==

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɔɪst|-ɔɪst]]

===Noun===
'''joist'''
# A piece of [[timber]] laid [[horizontal]]ly, or nearly so, to which the [[plank]]s of the floor, or the [[lath]]s or furring strips of a ceiling, are nailed; -- called, according to its position or use, [[binding joist]], [[bridging joist]], [[ceiling joist]], [[trimming joist]], etc.

===Verb===
{{en-infl-reg-consonant|joist||}}
# {{transitive}} To [[fit]] or [[furnish]] with joists.

